chunks.html_content:
Create or sign a petition that asks for a change to the law or to government policy.

After 10,000 signatures, petitions get a response from the government.

After 100,000 signatures, petitions are considered for debate in Parliament.
chunks.plain_content:
Petition Parliament and the government
Create or sign a petition that asks for a change to the law or to government policy.
After 10,000 signatures, petitions get a response from the government.
After 100,000 signatures, petitions are considered for debate in Parliament.

chunks.html_content: There’s a different way to petition Scottish Parliament and petition Welsh Parliament.
chunks.plain_content:
Petition Parliament and the government
There’s a different way to petition Scottish Parliament and petition Welsh Parliament.

chunks.html_content:
You must be a British citizen or a UK resident to create or sign a petition.

You cannot use this service to create a petition:

  • about something that Parliament or the government isn’t responsible for
  • about a legal case that’s active in the UK courts
  • that names people working in public bodies (except for senior management)

You can also petition Parliament through your MP.
